
[1]torch-thistle

   TORCH'-THISTLE, n. A plant of the genus Cactus.common name of a
   subdivision of the genus Cactus, called also cereus, from cera, wax,
   from the resemblance of the stems to a wax candle. Torch-thistle is
   from the prickly stems, used by the Indians for torches.
